                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.51/1309.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">American Chargé d’Affaires at London</gloss>.</hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d177fn1">Same to American Embassy, Berlin.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-02-23T22:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 23, 1913—10 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Department understands that the present halt in China loan negotiations is
                    due to renewed discussion between Great Britain and Germany regarding adviser
                    for salt gabelle. Ascertain and report promptly views of Foreign Office as to
                    prospects early signature of loan.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
